net.markenwerk.utils.data.fetcher

Class BaseFetchProgressListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.markenwerk.utils.data.fetcher.BaseFetchProgressListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FetchProgressListener

    public abstract class BaseFetchProgressListener
extends Object
implements FetchProgressListener
    A BaseFetchProgressListener is an implementation of FetchProgressListener with empty methods. It is intended a base for custom FetchProgressListener implementations, that don't need to implement all methods.
    Since:
    2.1.0
    Author:
    Torsten Krause (tk at markenwerk dot net)

      • onFetchProgress

        public void onFetchProgress(long bytesFetched)
        Description copied from interface: FetchProgressListener
        Indicates that the process of fetching bytes from an InputStream has progressed.

        The progress will only be reported if the Fetcher is capable of monitoring the progress.

        Specified by:
        onFetchProgress in interface FetchProgressListener
        Parameters:
        bytesFetched - Total amount of bytes fetched so far.

      • onFetchFailed

        public void onFetchFailed(FetchException exception,
                          Long bytesFetched)
        Description copied from interface: FetchProgressListener
        Indicates that the process of fetching bytes from an InputStream has failed.
        Specified by:
        onFetchFailed in interface FetchProgressListener
        Parameters:
        exception - The FetchException that caused the process to fail. This is the same FetchException that is thrown in the failing method of Fetcher that this FetchProgressListener has been given to.
        bytesFetched - Total total amount of bytes fetched before the process failed or null, if the Fetcher is not capable of monitoring the progress.

      • onFetchFinished

        public void onFetchFinished()
        Description copied from interface: FetchProgressListener
        Indicates that the process of fetching bytes from an InputStream has finished.

        This method will be called after either FetchProgressListener.onFetchSuccedded(Long) or FetchProgressListener.onFetchFailed(FetchException, Long) has been called.

        Specified by:
        onFetchFinished in interface FetchProgressListener
